Definition.WordDefinition: Complimentary \Com`pli*men"ta*ry\, a. Expressive of regard or praise; of the nature of, or containing, a compliment; as, a complimentary remark; a complimentary ticket. ``Complimentary addresses.'' --Prescott. [1913 Webster]

complimentary adj 1: conveying or resembling a compliment; "a complimentary remark" [ant: {uncomplimentary}] 2: costing nothing; "complimentary tickets" [syn: {costless}, {free}, {gratis(p)}, {gratuitous}]
